#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:1 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:1
msgid "How Dates Work"
msgstr "날짜의 작동 방식"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:4 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:4
msgid "Dates are a central focus of the Security Force Monitor's data and methodology. All claims in the Security Force Monitor dataset are time-bound."
msgstr "날짜는 'Security Force Monitor'의 데이터와 방법론에서 핵심적인 비중을 차지합니다. 'Security Force Monitor' 데이터셋에 포함된 모든 주장은 특정 시점과 결부되어 있습니다."

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:6 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:6
msgid "We structure all dates into ranges with a first and last date. The first date in the range can be the "start" and the last date can be the "end" of the range. Even a single day, such as May 5, 2025 (or 5 May 2025) would be entered with a first date of 2025-05-05 and a last date of 2025-05-05. All dates should be entered in the YYYY-MM-DD format."
msgstr "모든 날짜는 시작일과 종료일을 포함하는 범위 형태로 구성됩니다. 범위 내의 첫 번째 날짜는 '시작일'이 되고 마지막 날짜는 '종료일'이 됩니다. 2025년 5월 5일과 같은 단 하루의 경우에도 시작일은 2025-05-05, 종료일은 2025-05-05로 입력해야 합니다. 모든 날짜는 YYYY-MM-DD 형식으로 입력해야 합니다."

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:9 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:9
msgid "Precise ranges"
msgstr "정밀 범위"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:12 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:12
msgid "For a precise range all of the details of the claim are true for all dates in the range. A single day is a precise range with the first and last dates having the same date entered as a value in both ``first_precise:range`` and ``last_precise:range`` fields."
msgstr "'정확한 범위(precise range)'란 해당 범위 내의 모든 날짜에 대해 청구(claim)의 모든 세부 사항이 유효한 경우를 의미합니다. 단 하루의 경우, 시작일과 종료일 모두에 동일한 날짜를 입력함으로써 정확한 범위로 설정할 수 있습니다 ``first_precise:range`` 그리고 ``last_precise:range`` 필드들"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:14 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:14
msgid "Example"
msgstr "예"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:16 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:16
msgid "A citation states "John Smith was appointed commander of the 1 Brigade on 2014-08-01." To structure this sentence into data we'd pull out multiple claims:"
msgstr "어떤 인용문이 "존 스미스(John Smith)는 2014년 8월 1일 제1여단장으로 임명되었다"라고 명시하고 있다면, 이 문장을 데이터로 구조화하기 위해 다음과 같이 여러 개의 주장(claim)을 추출해낼 수 있습니다."

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:18 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:18
msgid "**unit**"
msgstr "**부대**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:20 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:20
msgid "``1 Brigade`` (entry for :ref:`name:annotation <unit-name-annotation>` and :ref:`unit:names:assertion`) would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2014-08-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2014-08-01``, with the ``starting:range`` of ``N`` and ``ending:range`` of ``N``."
msgstr "``제1여단`` (:ref:`name:annotation <unit-name-annotation>` 및 :ref:`unit:names:assertion` 항목)의 경우, ``first_precise:range`` ``2014-08-01`` 및 ``2014-08-01`` 의 ``last_precise:range`` 와, ``N`` 의 ``starting:range`` 및 ``N`` 의 ``ending:range``."

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:22 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:22
msgid "**person**"
msgstr "**사람**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:24 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:24
msgid "``John Smith`` (entry for :ref:`name:annotation <person-name-annotation>` and :ref:`person:names:assertion`) would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2014-08-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2014-08-01``, with the ``starting:range`` of ``N`` and ``ending:range`` of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:26 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:26
msgid "**posting**"
msgstr "**직책**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:28 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:28
msgid "``John Smith`` as part of ``1 Brigade`` has :ref:`posting:roles:assertion` of ``Commander`` would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2014-08-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2014-08-01``, with the ``starting:range`` of ``Y`` and ``ending:range`` of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:30 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:30
msgid "In the example above the citation clearly states that the :ref:`posting` starts on a specific date of ``2014-08-01``. However, it does not indicate that the :ref:`person` was born on that day or that the :ref:`unit` was created on that day. Thus, the ``starting:range`` for the :ref:`person` and :ref:`unit` is ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:32 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:32
msgid "The date of publication of the citation is always an important consideration when establishing date ranges for claims."
msgstr "청구항의 날짜 범위를 설정할 때 인용 문헌의 발행일은 항상 중요한 고려 사항입니다."

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:34 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:34
msgid "Example"
msgstr "예"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:36 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:36
msgid "A citation published on 2023-11-05 states "Xavier Johnson, commander of the 9 Battalion, discussed recent operations with reporters today. Since Johnson became commander on November 1st there have been a steady tempo of operations throughout Southern District." This citation would evidence the following claims:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:38 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:38
msgid "**unit**"
msgstr "**부대**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:40 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:40
msgid "``9 Battalion`` (entry for :ref:`name:annotation <unit-name-annotation>` and :ref:`unit:names:assertion`) would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2023-11-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2023-11-05``, with the ``starting:range`` of ``N`` and ``ending:range`` of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:42 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:42
msgid "**positioning**"
msgstr "**위치**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:44 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:44
msgid "``9 Battalion`` in ``Southern District`` with :ref:`positioning:types:assertion` of ``aoo`` would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2023-11-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2023-11-05``, with the ``starting:range`` of ``N`` and ``ending:range`` of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:46 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:46
msgid "**person**"
msgstr "**사람**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:48 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:48
msgid "``Xavier Johnson`` (entry for :ref:`name:annotation <person-name-annotation>` and :ref:`person:names:assertion`) would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2023-11-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2023-11-05``, with the ``starting:range`` of ``N`` and ``ending:range`` of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:50 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:50
msgid "**posting**"
msgstr "**직책**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:52 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:52
msgid "``Xavier Johnson`` as part of ``9 Battalion`` with :ref:`posting:roles:assertion` of ``Commander`` would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2023-11-011`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2023-11-05``, with the ``starting:range`` of ``Y`` and ``ending:range`` of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:54 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:54
msgid "In the example above the ``last_precise:range`` is established based on the date of publication of the citation, whereas the ``first_precise:range`` is explicitly stated in the text of the citation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:58 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:58
msgid "Imprecise ranges"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:61 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:61
msgid "For an imprecise range the details of the claim were true for at least one day in the range. Imprecise ranges give the ability to accurately capture ambiguity with dates in the data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:63 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:63
msgid "Example"
msgstr "예"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:65 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:65
msgid "A citation published on 2024-03-24 states "The 15 Regiment quickly responded to the attack on February 15th, conducting operations in several nearby areas, including Western, Upper, Lower and Central-South Governorates." The precise dates when the regiment was conducting these operations in any of the governorates is not clearly stated, however, we can establish an imprecise range for all of these positionings. For all of these positionings the ``first_imprecise:range`` would be ``2024-02-15`` and ``last_imprecise:range`` would be ``2024-03-24`` (the date of publication of the citation)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:67 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:67
msgid "The above example illustrates an important aspect of coding dates as ranges as opposed to collapsing dates into a singular value with "fuzzy dates" such as ``February 2024``. Fuzzy dates create major problems for these types of imprecise claims by "stretching" the time range of the data beyond what the underlying citation actually is claiming. Using a "fuzzy date" of ``February 2024`` would mean the regiment could have been conducting operations in the four governorates *before* the attack on February 15th - something the citation explicitly does not evidence. Similarly, a "fuzzy-date" approach would introduce errors for the last date which using "fuzzy-dates" could be entered as ``March 2024``. Taking that approach stretches the claim beyond what the citation evidences as it projects into the future, after the citation was published. To avoid either scenario Security Force Monitor enters dates as a range with full YYYY-MM-DD values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:69 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:69
msgid "Often citations will have claims which effectively translate to "at some point in time before this citation was published.""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:71 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:71
msgid "Example"
msgstr "예"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:73 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:73
msgid "A citation states that John Smith was appointed commander of the 1 Brigade on 2014-08-01. The citation also states that "John Smith previously commanded the 8 Battalion.""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:75 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:75
msgid "The scope of "previously" may appear unclear, but with imprecise ranges we can faithfully capture the time-bound claim being made. The value of ``since_beginning_of_time`` may be entered in the ``first_imprecise:range`` field to capture the scale of "previously" or similar statements from citations which, put another way, mean "at some point in time before the date of publication this claim was true." In the case of the example above, the :ref:`posting` of ``John Smith`` to the ``8 Battalion`` would have a ``first_imprecise:range`` of ``since_beginning_of_time`` and a ``last_imprecise:range`` of ``2014-08-01``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:78 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:78
msgid "Connecting Precise and Imprecise ranges"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:81 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:81
msgid "Often citations have a combination of precise and imprecise time-bound claims which must be carefully identified to properly enter into the dataset. When a claim has both a precise and imprecise range these must be entered so that there is a seamless date range that connects both ranges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:83 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:83
msgid "Example"
msgstr "예"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:85 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:85
msgid "A citation published on 2005-06-03 states: "Steven Wendell met with local officials at the 165 Battalion's headquarters today. Wendell, who was appointed as battalion commander last month, addressed concerns about security for the coming election season.""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:87 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:87
msgid "**unit**"
msgstr "**부대**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:89 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:89
msgid "``165 Battalion`` (entry for :ref:`name:annotation <unit-name-annotation>` and :ref:`unit:names:assertion`) would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2005-06-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2005-06-03``, as well as a ``first_imprecise:range`` of ``2005-05-01`` and ``last_imprecise:range`` of ``2005-05-31``. The ``starting:range`` and ``ending:range`` would both have an entry of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:91 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:91
msgid "**person**"
msgstr "**사람**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:93 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:93
msgid "``Xavier Johnson`` (entry for :ref:`name:annotation <person-name-annotation>` and :ref:`person:names:assertion`) would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2005-06-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2005-06-03``, as well as a ``first_imprecise:range`` of ``2005-05-01`` and ``last_imprecise:range`` of ``2005-05-31``. The ``starting:range`` and ``ending:range`` would both have an entry of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:95 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:95
msgid "**posting**"
msgstr "**직책**"

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:97 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:97
msgid "``Xavier Johnson`` as part of ``9 Battalion`` with :ref:`posting:roles:assertion` of ``Commander`` would have a ``first_precise:range`` of ``2005-06-01`` and ``last_precise:range`` of ``2005-06-03``, as well as a ``first_imprecise:range`` of ``2005-05-01`` and ``last_imprecise:range`` of ``2005-05-31``. The ``starting:range`` would have a value of ``Y`` and ``ending:range`` a value of ``N``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:100 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:100
msgid ".. note::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:102 ../../source/how-dates-work.rst:102
msgid "Our article :ref:`Establishing Contiguous or Non-Contiguous Claims` provides extended guidance to help researchers decisions about whether a timeline is continuous or not."
msgstr "저희 논문 :ref:`Establishing Contiguous or Non-Contiguous Claims` 는 연구자들이 타임라인의 연속성 여부를 판단하는 데 도움이 되는 상세한 지침을 제공합니다."
